	"name": "Vicar",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow-white.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Your devotion to your patron deity is absolute, and you have been granted additional authority in recognition of this devotion. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>Your Constitution or Wisdom score increases by +1, to a maximum of 20.</p></li><li><p>You gain proficiency with the Religion skill if you are not already proficient or gain an expertise die if you are. Additionally, you gain two Religion skill specialties. They do not count against your skill specialties known.</p></li><li><p>You can choose a second @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.0dwsf82gco1j8ghu]{Principle of Devotion} option if you desire.</p></li><li><p>Choose a 1st- or 2nd- level cleric spell with at least one rare variant. You learn a rare variant of the selected spell for free. You only need to prepare the base version of the selected spell and can choose to cast either the rare or base variant as you see fit when casting it.</p></li></ul>",
